                    <comment id="12845318" author="rcmuir" created="Mon, 15 Mar 2010 14:11:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attached is a very small patch to the Solr branch so it will compile against flex jars.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12845332" author="mikemccand" created="Mon, 15 Mar 2010 14:40:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So awesome that we are at the point where we can do this!  Thanks Robert...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12845487" author="mikemccand" created="Mon, 15 Mar 2010 19:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The bug was... if you asked for TermsEnum on a non-existent field on a foreign IndexReader (like Solr&apos;s, SolrIndexReader), so that the &quot;emulate flex API on top of non-flex API&quot; layer is used, then the returned TermsEnum would incorrectly return 1 term, and then null, when it should&apos;ve returned null right off.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit shortly &amp;#8211; simple fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With this all Solr&apos;s tests pass when you drop in the flex JARs!!  Yay.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12845488" author="mikemccand" created="Mon, 15 Mar 2010 20:03:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Solr can now run on flex &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
